The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to clustering and location, which are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of LP-rounding and objective-oblivious clustering techniques also suggests a connection to optimization (cs.DS) and combinatorial algorithms (cs.DM).
